## un-punt — cleanup conventions

This repo uses [un-punt](https://github.com/un-punt/un-punt) to capture deferrals (TODOs, `as any`, skipped tests, etc.) during your work and propose verified cleanup passes at natural stopping points (end of feature, area switch, end of session). The skill does this silently as a side effect of normal coding — you should not have to invoke it. State lives in `.un-punt/` (gitignored by default). When the skill suggests a sweep, the workflow is **Refuse > Flag > Fix**: the agent prefers to refuse or flag uncertain work over attempting a fix; nothing lands on your branch without the disposition prompt at sweep end. Trust contract details and per-repo overrides live in `.un-punt/contract.md`.
